Class SearchFragment

  • java.lang.Object
    • androidx.fragment.app.Fragment
      • com.cmput3owo1.moodlet.fragments.SearchFragment
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    android.content.ComponentCallbacks, android.view.View.OnCreateContextMenuListener, android.widget.SearchView.OnQueryTextListener, androidx.lifecycle.LifecycleOwner, androidx.lifecycle.ViewModelStoreOwner, androidx.savedstate.SavedStateRegistryOwner, UserListAdapter.OnFollowClickListener, IUserServiceProvider.OnFollowRequestListener, IUserServiceProvider.OnUserSearchListener

    public class SearchFragment
extends androidx.fragment.app.Fragment
implements android.widget.SearchView.OnQueryTextListener, UserListAdapter.OnFollowClickListener, IUserServiceProvider.OnUserSearchListener, IUserServiceProvider.OnFollowRequestListener
    A fragment that holds the Search/Discover functionality. App users can search for other app users to follow, and can send them a follow request. This fragment displays a search bar, and the user can type in text to search for. A list of User objects with a prefix matching the search text is displayed under.
